Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.27,0:27:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, thank you very much. Yeah. Past life regression can be a very, very interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.99,0:27:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,experience. Thank you very much. Hello. Sometimes I struggle with trying to find the difference
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.78,0:27:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,between going through an experience and juicing it. So I was wondering if you could elaborate
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.19,0:27:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on that a bit. Juicing it is when you're purposely utilizing it for some secondary
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.00,0:27:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,gain. There's a secondary gain. So to relinquish it, all you have to do is spot what is the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.96,0:27:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,secondary gain and be willing to surrender the secondary gain. Don't forget, in return
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.98,0:28:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for surrendering, the secondary gain of that which is negative, in return, you get the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.15,0:28:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,positive gain of that which is positive. So you feel better about yourself when you've
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.82,0:28:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiven somebody, even though they did actually, you know, did do something wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.05,0:28:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you do by harboring the resentment. So the ego is reluctant to give it up because
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.54,0:28:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it thinks I'm giving up all this wonderful juice of hate and resentment and feeling sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.23,0:28:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,for myself in return for nothing. No, you get something back. And after you do it a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.19,0:28:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,few times and find that you feel much better about yourself than you did before you let
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.13,0:28:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it go, it then becomes easier each time. Every time you let that resentment go, you feel
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.36,0:28:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,better than you did when you were having the resentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.25,0:28:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,For one thing, you don't have the guilt to contend with. And so you receive a benefit
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.00,0:28:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,from the letting it go. And after you do that a few times, you feel freer and higher and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.11,0:29:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,better and happier, and you realize that it was worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.11,0:29:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Dr. Hawkins. It's a privilege to be here, and I'm very honored. My question, this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.92,0:29:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you said, God's will for us is free choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.79,0:29:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,God's will for us is free choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.11,0:29:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,God's will for us is free choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.96,0:29:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, free choice, yes. Freedom is a basic spiritual reality universe. So that way there
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.79,0:29:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,would be no accountability, and there could be no spiritual progression.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.33,0:30:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Does God have a plan for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.50,0:30:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Does God have a plan for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.38,0:30:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be answered in the way that you put the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.16,0:30:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.18,0:30:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a deterministic contextualization that you've given.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.24,0:30:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.29,0:30:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the reality, out of the ultimate reality, emerges a creation with its own intrinsic
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.54,0:30:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,nature. So there isn't a you God that dictates that this condition for a you person, you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.05,0:30:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,understand? It's more like out of this arises the whole panorama of all that is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.02,0:30:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And now as you as a spiritual reality have all these choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.61,0:30:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.83,0:30:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That God presents you with a whole carnival of options, you know? Not as a person, God,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.48,0:31:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,giving a person to you that, but out of the sheer reality of that which has been created,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.27,0:31:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,opens up options for all that lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.34,0:31:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.60,0:31:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Wish to express my heartfelt gratitude for all that is in the field at this moment and all that have
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.36,0:31:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,contributed to this possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.74,0:31:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been a student of yours since the beginning of the millennium.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.85,0:31:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been a student of yours since the beginning of the millennium.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.00,0:31:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the opportunity now to be in your presence three times.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.48,0:31:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And every time I've been before you before or in your presence, that the answers to the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.16,0:31:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,questions I've developed have all formulated and I've not had the opportunity to come up
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.55,0:31:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,or the reason to come up and see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.00,0:32:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The question I pose is, coming from a space of non-duality and totally non-positionality,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.23,0:32:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,how does one make a stand for truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.02,0:32:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's a whole lecture in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.95,0:32:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But without positionality, you merely stand being what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.48,0:32:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the eagle stands being an eagle, not in order to scare doves, not in order to,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.41,0:32:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,not for any reason at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.73,0:32:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It just is an eagle because that's fulfilling its eagle nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.71,0:32:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.09,0:32:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you stand for truth, it's not like you're standing in opposition to falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.77,0:32:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You're merely standing for truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.75,0:32:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.02,0:32:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.53,0:33:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.53,0:33:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.96,0:33:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a strength to stand for the truth as you understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.46,0:33:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,To do so by being it, not to please anyone or to accomplish.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.91,0:33:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, there's no purpose to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.50,0:33:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just because that's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.72,0:33:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So I have a certain obligation as a teacher, is my understanding of it, to fulfill that,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.57,0:33:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to fulfill that, to have the strength to do so, not for any particular reason except to fulfill
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.24,0:33:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,one's purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.44,0:33:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all about one's potential, which is all that God really gives us, is potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.18,0:33:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And my understanding would be an appreciation for the gift of the potential to fulfill it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.11,0:33:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to the best of your capacity, and thus to serve God.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.88,0:34:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That might be by being the best athlete, the best cab driver, a good husband, good father,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.57,0:34:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiving citizen.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.92,0:34:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows what it means, because at each level it means something different.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.90,0:34:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.86,0:34:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.32,0:34:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.55,0:34:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.61,0:34:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.67,0:34:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.73,0:34:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.80,0:34:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.84,0:34:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.90,0:34:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we, what can we do to encourage our grandchildren to develop an interest in
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.13,0:34:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,spirituality, since we see them seldom?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.42,0:34:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you see them very often?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.92,0:34:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple times a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.13,0:34:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you attract them, you try to attract them into things you think would be contributory
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.19,0:34:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to that direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.61,0:34:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We went over some of them this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.80,0:34:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Appreciation for beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.86,0:35:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandmother used to read me Shakespeare, and my mother would take me to the opera.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.07,0:35:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And my father would take us to the ballet.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.17,0:35:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And they would take us to the aquarium.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.34,0:35:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And they would take us to the, in Chicago, the Museum of Science and Industry, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.88,0:35:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,planetarium.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.17,0:35:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And I joined the Art Institute.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.73,0:35:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So those things were all endeavors encouraged by the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.34,0:35:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, they valued aesthetics, and learning, and wisdom, appreciation of nature and beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.32,0:35:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So you encourage them in the direction of things that you think,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.48,0:35:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,help build character, join the scouts, you know. I still look at people around me,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.57,0:35:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,they go on trips, they're completely unprepared, and I say, didn't they ever go
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.82,0:35:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to scouts? Where were you when they passed out? Be prepared. So you encourage them
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.94,0:36:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,into things that will carry them in the direction you want them to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.11,0:36:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah? Thank you. Appreciation for beauty and all such things. Thank you. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.28,0:36:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Aesthetics. Aesthetics. Sensitivity for aesthetics will result in a
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.19,0:36:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,disinclination to anything criminal. People who've had high exposure to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.13,0:36:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,aesthetics practically never become criminal. Almost never. I never heard of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.23,0:36:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody who played the violin for 30 years and then killed his grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.36,0:36:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You know? It just goes against your aesthetic grain.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.59,0:36:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.92,0:36:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Dr. Hawkins. I was raised as a Catholic and I struggle with what I think
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.59,0:37:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you've termed as a fear of the judge. Fear of judgment. Fear, yeah. Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.51,0:37:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm just wondering, I guess I would like that to go away. Will it ever go
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.78,0:37:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,away, that fear? Or will I just, will it just kind of recede as I
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.80,0:37:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,continue to work with... You have to have greater faith in the infinite mercy of God, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.03,0:37:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In the fact that God can see the defect of character. And therefore, there's a difference
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.19,0:37:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,between culpability and responsibility. They could learn to differentiate responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.86,0:37:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and culpability. You can be responsible but hardly culpable because you don't have that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.01,0:37:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,much brains to be that culpable. You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.61,0:37:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.26,0:37:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Culpability would mean that you were of a very advanced capacity for understanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.30,0:38:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and then chose to defy God, which is a different thing. See? You're not capable of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.55,0:38:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't think I have defied God?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.26,0:38:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not even capable of it, you know. You're not about to defy God in any way that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.51,0:38:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand God.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.96,0:38:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.96,0:38:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No. The childish fears of God, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.05,0:38:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.42,0:38:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And spiritual counseling of spiritual counsel.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.07,0:38:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.15,0:38:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,they should have gotten you over that by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.15,0:38:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They used to have me see a priest about scrupulosity, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.15,0:38:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I thought every sin showed up like on a glass plate behind you,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.15,0:38:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, and God could see this spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.15,0:38:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And I told you at the time I was gone the way that you're supposed to go to communion,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.40,0:38:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you're supposed to go to confession Saturday afternoon as late as possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.40,0:38:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so as few hours as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.53,0:38:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you go to the earliest communions in the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.53,0:38:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so there's very few hours in which your sin might get given by eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.53,0:38:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell you, I'm on my way to communion,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.40,0:38:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's a 30-foot Swanson swimming suit I had with this lady in a swimming suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.40,0:39:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I told the old boy nothing but steroids run through his veins, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.25,0:39:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the 30 feet of feminine pulchritude, and I'm on my way to confession.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.25,0:39:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.25,0:39:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Communion.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.17,0:39:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So I quickly shut off all my thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.17,0:39:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried not to look at this 30-foot lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.17,0:39:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,30-foot long Swanson swimming suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.26,0:39:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The top is down on the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.26,0:39:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,29 Model A Ford, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.26,0:39:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I try not, I avert my eyes in the other direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.90,0:39:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know if a sinful thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.90,0:39:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I was scared that a sinful thought might have gone by without my even realizing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.21,0:39:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had fear and trepidation when I went for communion.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.21,0:39:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought when they pass the cup, if I take a drink out of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.21,0:39:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe lightning will strike me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.65,0:39:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, I had to go for counseling
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.82,0:39:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to develop a reasonable conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.82,0:39:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So you maybe have a hypertrophy conscience,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.82,0:40:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,leftover from childhood, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.82,0:40:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And maybe a couple of sessions with the priest
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.82,0:40:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to help you get a more reasonable conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.82,0:40:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what's the fear that comes up at the final doorway then?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.82,0:40:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a different fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.82,0:40:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's a different lady that didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.82,0:40:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's totally different.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.82,0:40:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It had nothing to do with sin and guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.82,0:40:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear was there was nothing left.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.63,0:40:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a very high space.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.63,0:40:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody, hardly anybody had ever been there.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.63,0:40:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you only knew, I saw who'd been there.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.63,0:40:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And then came the last attraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.03,0:40:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All power, all power is yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.03,0:40:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Own it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.32,0:40:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you know you're not accountable,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.32,0:40:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're not, that you're free of all the things that you feared,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.32,0:40:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are far beyond that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.32,0:40:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All power is yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.32,0:40:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Claim it, own it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.84,0:40:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw who had said yes and who had said no.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.90,0:40:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was ridiculous because at the time I was all that power.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.90,0:40:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I want that which I am already?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.00,0:41:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was completely the everythingness of all possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.00,0:41:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There was only one last thing to lay down before God.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.59,0:41:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And that came to me as the next realization.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.59,0:41:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That I laid everything and surrendered all except life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.61,0:41:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought this too, this too.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.51,0:41:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything had to be laid before God.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.51,0:41:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I laid ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.51,0:41:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I laid bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.51,0:41:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I laid serenity.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.69,0:41:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.69,0:41:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,All things.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.21,0:41:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The last thing that remained was life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.78,0:41:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Sense of life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.13,0:41:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That this too must be laid before the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.13,0:41:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So at that point I laid my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.51,0:41:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This to thee, O Lord, to which I surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.15,0:41:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That which I believe is my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.80,0:42:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you see the core of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.80,0:42:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it is convinced it is the source of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.80,0:42:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has been since the beginning of life on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.80,0:42:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And so then I did surrender my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.48,0:42:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then a terror came up.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.96,0:42:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.96,0:42:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A strong terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.76,0:42:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.88,0:42:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And I died.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.88,0:42:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You actually die.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.88,0:42:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.88,0:42:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You actually go with the agony of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.21,0:42:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You've never been through the agony of death before.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.21,0:42:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You all just left the body in order to avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.55,0:42:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And then came the agony of death itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.55,0:42:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Anguish.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.55,0:42:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.55,0:42:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And beyond that was then.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.92,0:42:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The revelation of infinite glory beyond all description.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.17,0:42:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Forevermore.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.17,0:42:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It only has to be gone through once.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.67,0:43:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's never been gone through before.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.67,0:43:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You can die hundreds of times and never go through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.67,0:43:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But it came up.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.46,0:43:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.26,0:43:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Also it brought up the fear of non-existence for its final run.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.92,0:43:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Which I was born with at age three.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.48,0:43:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And which had recurred later at level 850 of
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.48,0:43:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Mesha.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.30,0:43:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That constantly surrendering the linear brings you to nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.30,0:43:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But when the nothingness came back this time I knew it was the Void.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.30,0:43:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it was not the ultimate reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.30,0:43:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When I'd left other lifetimes as the hinata Buddhist I would arrive at the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.30,0:43:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And that'd be it for that lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.30,0:43:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This time because I'd had the experience in the snow bank of the presence of god.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.44,0:43:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized the absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.07,0:43:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like an infinite nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.32,0:43:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in comparison to an infinite everythingness of God
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.92,0:43:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as absolute bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.92,0:44:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, realizing the mistake,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.92,0:44:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I backed out of it because the presence of God
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.61,0:44:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is signified by a profound and infinite love.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.76,0:44:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Profound, staggeringly, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.34,0:44:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, there's no mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.88,0:44:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.88,0:44:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.71,0:44:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah? Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.57,0:44:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting question.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.46,0:44:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, I was raised a Catholic, like that lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.82,0:44:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And I went to Marquette University in Milwaukee.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.76,0:44:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.67,0:44:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And I studied theology.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.17,0:44:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.01,0:44:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And I didn't get all A's, like you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.01,0:44:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You what?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.84,0:44:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't get everything like you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.44,0:44:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.76,0:44:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've tried to make up for that since.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.90,0:44:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.75,0:45:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And done a lot of studying.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.09,0:45:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just theology, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.55,0:45:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Just theology.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.38,0:45:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.09,0:45:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I've studied your work and I've read your story
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.69,0:45:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,many times. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.94,0:45:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And heard you talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.48,0:45:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've also read the stories of many of the mystics
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.76,0:45:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and saints, especially the Catholic ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.19,0:45:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the themes that seems to run through
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.48,0:45:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,those stories is this depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.15,0:45:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You describe being depressed for a long period.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.15,0:45:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, very profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.11,0:45:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And many of the saints describe that depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.53,0:45:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.38,0:45:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm just wondering if depression is part of
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.96,0:45:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what we have to look forward to in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.96,0:45:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the struggle, depression is inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.36,0:45:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.19,0:45:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All the Christian mystics describe states
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.82,0:45:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,when that spirit seems to leave you and you leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.73,0:45:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you, my beloved, leave me?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.88,0:45:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Like one has been deserted by one's lover, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.11,0:46:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,A very profound state.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.57,0:46:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But you work it through, it's just a condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.63,0:46:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.46,0:46:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.30,0:46:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a cognition?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.21,0:46:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.05,0:46:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You said it's a cognition?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.98,0:46:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not a cognition, it's affective, affective.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.69,0:46:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A affective state.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.61,0:46:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm terrified of facing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.71,0:46:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like it's blocking my progress
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.55,0:46:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because I don't want to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.46,0:46:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh, well, it's some other lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.42,0:46:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Put it off till another lifetime?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.26,0:46:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.11,0:46:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.42,0:46:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Your faith and love of God becomes sufficient
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.71,0:46:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're willing to go through that for thee, O Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.57,0:46:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.40,0:46:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,For thee, O Lord, do I face it?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.30,0:46:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I face this within myself
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.73,0:46:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and I ask for your help and strength, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.80,0:46:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,To look at the nothingness at the bottom of the depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.46,0:47:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling of worthlessness, whatever it may be,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.67,0:47:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that you failed God in some way, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.73,0:47:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So you ask God's help and you just walk right through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.44,0:47:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,At the other end is salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.67,0:47:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So if it led to hell, I would tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.00,0:47:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.32,0:47:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't lead to hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.86,0:47:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I've been through as bad as you can go through.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.44,0:47:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't lead you to hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.28,0:47:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It leads you away from hell, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.65,0:47:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You're fearing hell, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.46,0:47:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon me?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.30,0:47:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the higher levels of hell are anguish, depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.80,0:47:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.63,0:47:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.46,0:47:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but they're not based on a reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.59,0:47:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so they're safe to walk through, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.82,0:47:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.65,0:48:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you come out and you're free of it forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.30,0:48:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, thank you for the compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.55,0:48:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been very helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.13,0:48:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is regarding the mind being 99% silent
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.07,0:48:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and 1% hypnotized.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.46,0:48:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind being 99% silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.17,0:48:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes, yes, yes, yes, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.44,0:48:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What actually has the power to induce mind
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.44,0:48:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,into state of hypnosis, and is it this state of hypnosis
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.34,0:48:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,through spiritual work I try to awaken from?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.11,0:48:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego is prone to suggestibility and to entrapment.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.98,0:48:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very easy to seduce the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.11,0:48:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a whole slide we didn't get to,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.17,0:49:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the seduction of the ego by the novelty, the circus,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.53,0:49:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the carnival that goes on, you see, emotions and concepts.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.00,0:49:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind gets glamorized by the drama of all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.65,0:49:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets hypnotized by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.84,0:49:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When there's a little accident by the side of the road,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.78,0:49:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the traffic backs up for miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.00,0:49:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing but a dented fender, a dented fender,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.09,0:49:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're backed up for miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.42,0:49:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,See that?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.28,0:49:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can see through the illusion of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.03,0:49:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,then you're free of it to travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.86,0:49:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.26,0:49:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to watch for the seduction of the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.55,0:49:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,by the bizarre, the seduction of the mind by tragedy,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.26,0:49:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the seduction of the mind by oh, oh, isn't that terrible?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.15,0:50:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are all seductions.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.13,0:50:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to refuse the seduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.23,0:50:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The seduction of the mind by tragedy, the widow,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.17,0:50:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole sad story.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.57,0:50:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's got a sad story.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.23,0:50:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's got a sad story.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.88,0:50:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.84,0:50:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, in Power Versus Force, in Power in Space,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.28,0:50:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in the sports chapter, you write about Roger Bannister's
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.17,0:50:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,four-minute mile record.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.75,0:50:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And you mentioned that he was running for humankind
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.07,0:50:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than for his own glory.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.15,0:50:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've always been very interested in having someone
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.55,0:50:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,change the focus from competitive sports
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.19,0:51:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to non-competitive sports where you're
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.76,0:51:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,running against yourself instead of running against another team
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.03,0:51:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or another person.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.40,0:51:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah, uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.34,0:51:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think that endurance events like the marathon
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.86,0:51:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,may be the most useful for people to learn
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.88,0:51:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.38,0:51:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.34,0:51:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I was myself a marathon runner.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.50,0:51:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a marathon runner.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.51,0:51:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you get to mile 21 or 22 or whatever, you hit the wall
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.90,0:51:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and you feel that you just can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.36,0:51:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.09,0:51:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But then your intention pulls you through.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.78,0:51:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.59,0:51:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.09,0:51:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.59,0:51:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it's effortless.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.84,0:51:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.53,0:51:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you're being run.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.40,0:51:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.90,0:51:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So I learned firsthand the power of intention just by doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.40,0:51:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, great.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.90,0:51:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.40,0:51:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.90,0:51:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And in January 2000, I created a new marathon-type race
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.13,0:51:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from scratch to celebrate the new millennium.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.17,0:51:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And I coined the term millenathon,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.61,0:51:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and I called it the millenathons.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.13,0:51:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And we had the fastest field of women marathon runners
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.55,0:52:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,at any race that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.65,0:52:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But I also set a goal for myself to be a serial marathon.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.28,0:52:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So I ran 16 marathons in 16 months leading up to my race,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.28,0:52:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,partly to promote my race at these other events.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.78,0:52:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So I say all this to put my question into context.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.23,0:52:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking of a new project now, not to put on another race,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.30,0:52:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but to get some senior person who's 65 or 70 or older
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.15,0:52:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to run a record marathon time that's faster than the 50 years
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.86,0:52:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,old record.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.28,0:52:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And my question is, will some record like this
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.42,0:52:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,have a similar effect to Roger Bannister's four-minute mile?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.61,0:53:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I still don't get what's the purpose of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.36,0:53:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose is to show that one can do things from intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.59,0:53:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because we have all this talk about aging,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.88,0:53:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're over the hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.23,0:53:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.94,0:53:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as you've got plenty of doctors and nurses there
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.26,0:53:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,announcing it, I wouldn't want the liability, the lawsuits
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.25,0:53:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that are going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.40,0:53:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the second part of my question
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.80,0:53:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is that, do I myself have the capacity to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.19,0:53:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sure you've got the capacity to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.69,0:53:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you calibrate it?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.98,0:53:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, I'm just asking you to look at the wisdom of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.50,0:53:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You're soliciting aging people to press past lethal barriers,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.21,0:53:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm thinking the legal fallout would kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.46,0:53:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be the first to sue you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.50,0:53:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't mean that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.69,0:53:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I meant whether I could be the one to actually run the record time.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.82,0:53:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.92,0:53:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.19,0:54:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that's up to the, you're looking at it as causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.88,0:54:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's up to a multi-factors at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.42,0:54:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, why would you be interested in winning?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.40,0:54:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.01,0:54:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.25,0:54:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not winning, but running a record time to show that.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.84,0:54:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.84,0:54:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,To show that age doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.92,0:54:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, age doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.48,0:54:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If age didn't matter, you wouldn't be even there.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.05,0:54:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If you didn't think about it, you'd be too old for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.05,0:54:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Move from the linear to the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.48,0:54:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Do the same thing, though, with spiritual endeavor.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.92,0:54:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Run the spiritual race, yeah, that you can take with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.63,0:54:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The physical race you can't take with you when you leave this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.69,0:54:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.69,0:54:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your question.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.69,0:54:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.69,0:54:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.69,0:54:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I get the, I get the, I get the, I get the, I get the, I get the, I get the, I get the,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.69,0:54:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I get the, I get the, I get the, I get the, I get the, I get the, I get the, I get the, I get
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.69,0:54:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.69,0:54:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I get the, I get the, I get the, I get the, I get the, I get the, I get the.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.69,0:54:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.69,0:54:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.69,0:54:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the energy is wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.69,0:55:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Energy is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.84,0:55:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the energy's wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.84,0:55:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.84,0:55:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.15,0:55:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.48,0:55:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.48,0:55:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get a sign?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.48,0:55:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.48,0:55:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Dr. Atkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.48,0:55:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your presence here, the darshan of your eyes, it's appreciated.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.57,0:55:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what I hear from you today is a bit of a comment in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.78,0:55:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,For me it's like human form and the animal form, the human form is like an egg, a cocoon
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.21,0:55:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,for the soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.90,0:55:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Like at 200 we begin to break the shell and at 600 it's like we get out of the shell and
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.01,0:55:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we go and fly forever after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.03,0:55:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all this human process for soul, am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.19,0:56:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, 600 is set in the classic bliss state, in 600 you enter the enlightened states.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.57,0:56:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Could we have a glimpse of that and go back after or it's a permanent process when we
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.53,0:56:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,get there?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.63,0:56:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a permanent process?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.82,0:56:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we have a glimpse, an overview of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.57,0:56:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 600?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.57,0:56:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.98,0:56:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, can you get back from it?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.90,0:56:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I mean that can we have a glimpse, an overview of the 600 state and come back again?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.82,0:56:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about coming back again, in the level of 600 coming back again is not even
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.88,0:56:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.88,0:57:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're worrying about it from a different level.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.73,0:57:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're asking is a conundrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.32,0:57:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm getting to the point where I don't care if I live or die as a physical being when I
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.32,0:57:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,care about whether I live or die as a physical being.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.32,0:57:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No, because 600 is no longer a relevant question.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.32,0:57:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's because I mentioned that a lot of people leave there.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.05,0:57:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, about 50% will leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.05,0:57:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.26,0:57:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, on each level a high percent will leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.26,0:57:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's very few that makes it all the way through because most will leave the physicality
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.26,0:57:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.94,0:57:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it hard on your body to stay on this level?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.94,0:57:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.17,0:57:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.17,0:57:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a strain going up.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.05,0:57:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,When you start clearing the energy fields in the 800s or so, yes, it's a burning sensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.05,0:57:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's anything negative that you're holding in mind from the collective, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.05,0:57:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's an intolerable painful burning sensation like all through your aura.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.05,0:58:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So you research and find out what kind of an energy it is you're holding and clear it
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.44,0:58:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and purify it and then it disappears again.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.44,0:58:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.44,0:58:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.01,0:58:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you ever see that kind of light of things?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.01,0:58:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.01,0:58:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.01,0:58:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like a Christmas wreath.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.32,0:58:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.32,0:58:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you ever see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.32,0:58:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.32,0:58:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.34,0:58:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's around sometimes, around my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.34,0:58:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's a different thing that you're asking me.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.34,0:58:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The inner light, it has no configuration.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.34,0:58:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.34,0:58:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.34,0:58:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The inner light has no configuration.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.34,0:58:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.34,0:58:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a state of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.34,0:58:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a state of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.34,0:58:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A state of radiance of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.34,0:58:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.34,0:58:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.34,0:58:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.34,0:58:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I am from Montreal, so I'd like to know if somebody has any questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.34,0:58:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.40,0:58:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.40,0:58:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.40,0:58:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.40,0:58:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.40,0:58:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.73,0:58:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.73,0:58:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.73,0:58:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.73,0:58:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would like to know if someone near Montreal is around here so maybe we can meet
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.92,0:58:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and have...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.92,0:58:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a Montrealite around here, anybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.07,0:58:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.07,0:58:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.07,0:58:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There are some people from Canada.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.07,0:58:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.07,0:58:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.07,0:58:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.07,0:59:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.07,0:59:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, because...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.07,0:59:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.07,0:59:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.07,0:59:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to have a picture too.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.67,0:59:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.67,0:59:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.67,0:59:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a French accent?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.67,0:59:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I have a French accent.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.67,0:59:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a French accent?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.67,0:59:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You like the French accent?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.67,0:59:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I like the French accent.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.67,0:59:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.17,0:59:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.30,0:59:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it has a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.19,0:59:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,plaza to it
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.42,0:59:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain panache
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.71,0:59:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain panache
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.84,0:59:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I say
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.71,0:59:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you talked about
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.28,0:59:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,non-existence
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.98,0:59:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to cry
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.03,0:59:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and my question is
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.34,0:59:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,does
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.61,0:59:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,non-existence have
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.92,0:59:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.38,1:00:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,no
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.94,1:00:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so how are you rescued
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.44,1:00:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,from the pits of hell
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.13,1:00:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,by transcendence
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.00,1:00:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,not by non-existence
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.30,1:00:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,not by
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.80,1:00:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,by transcendence not by non-existence
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.90,1:00:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,no by potentiality
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.34,1:00:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,do you have the potential
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.23,1:00:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to be rescued
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.59,1:00:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is that something
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.25,1:00:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,so even in
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.25,1:00:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,non-existence
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.26,1:00:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not a reality
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.28,1:00:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can be
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.01,1:00:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,rescued from that
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.84,1:00:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,yes
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.17,1:00:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,okay
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.71,1:00:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise you would stay there
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.15,1:00:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,right
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.36,1:00:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,okay
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.53,1:00:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.46,1:00:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,yes there will be nothing
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.71,1:00:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring you back out of it
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.88,1:00:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing to realize the error
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.51,1:01:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.50,1:01:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a question
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.48,1:01:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I just came here
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.36,1:01:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to be
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.01,1:01:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting here across from you
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.34,1:01:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.63,1:01:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.82,1:01:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you for being my teacher
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.82,1:01:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.80,1:01:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,question I wanted to ask you
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.67,1:01:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is that
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.57,1:01:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you say that everything happens spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.96,1:01:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,including all human thought
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.48,1:01:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,happens spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.65,1:01:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is spontaneous emergence of potentiality into actuality
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.63,1:01:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on karmic propensities and local conditions
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.98,1:01:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and intention
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.65,1:01:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on context
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.48,1:02:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,so intention also plays a part in
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.21,1:02:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the likelihood of it manifestation
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.09,1:02:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,now how does that relate to free will
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.76,1:02:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the part that I want to ask you about
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.59,1:02:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a very interesting question
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.98,1:02:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and I could write you a whole chapter about it right now
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.30,1:02:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it has to do
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.17,1:02:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the non-linear are like prevailing energy levels
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.69,1:02:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the more powerful overshadow the lesser
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.17,1:02:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so the lesser operating within the overall larger field of the greater
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.15,1:02:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so by intention you've already set the greater
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.15,1:02:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,within that you have the exercise of the greater
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.59,1:02:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the more powerful the lesser operating overshadowed the lesser operating
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.17,1:02:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the idea
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.55,1:02:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand the complete discussion of free will
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.90,1:02:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,would take us a little while
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.01,1:02:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're setting propensities and likelihoods
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.78,1:02:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,this is interesting in advance theoretical physics
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.65,1:02:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that the more often you make a certain decision
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.26,1:02:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the more likely that decision will recur
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.46,1:03:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it's called the Zeno effect or something like that
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.67,1:03:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that likelihood increases
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.19,1:03:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,although it's not a cause and effect relationship
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.30,1:03:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it's that you're affecting the field
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.98,1:03:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so the field is the field of the field
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.78,1:03:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so the field is the field of the field
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.82,1:03:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so the field is the field of the field
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.92,1:03:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The field is one of likelihoods, so by choice you're setting up fields of progressive dominance
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.32,1:03:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the lesser field, although they're intrinsically independent, they are only operating
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.32,1:03:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,within a higher field.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.51,1:03:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's say if the highest field of your life is to serve God, then lesser decisions
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.15,1:03:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,about health or longevity and many other things will be subservient to that, how you see that
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.88,1:03:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,serves your overall life of request, you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.86,1:03:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I come all this way and go through all the trouble to come here and speak to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.19,1:03:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,all these people?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.19,1:03:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I can live without it, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.19,1:03:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sitting at home with my cat and I'm contented and happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.92,1:03:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I need?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.03,1:03:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Why in the world am I here?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.88,1:04:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the question we ask each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.86,1:04:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we do this thing or not?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.82,1:04:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So we say, well, what is the purpose of our knowing all the things we know except to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.44,1:04:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,share it with others?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.61,1:04:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the answer comes out, how do we better serve God?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.26,1:04:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So when this foundation asked us to come and speak, we both spoke to each other, what do
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.30,1:04:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.30,1:04:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She says, yes, well, yes, we should do so.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.86,1:04:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then to confirm it, we'll ask the arm, that serves us good, the arm says yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.40,1:04:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, depending on the context of what you think your most important role in life
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.05,1:04:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is, you see, if we had some young children at home who were sick, it might come out differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.00,1:04:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No, don't come.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.00,1:04:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.00,1:04:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It serves our good by staying home and helping the young children.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.11,1:04:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So it would depend on what stage of life, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.73,1:04:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to write a book or a chapter about free will and this subject?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.53,1:04:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Free will.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.53,1:04:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to write you a chapter in some book about free will.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.53,1:04:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.53,1:05:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little hard to contextualize.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.53,1:05:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I, as I said, I gave you a reference, three recent articles on intention, attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.17,1:05:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.17,1:05:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.23,1:05:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Attention set.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.23,1:05:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Medina.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.23,1:05:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,M-E-D-I-N-A.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.23,1:05:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It appeared in the last three issues of Psychiatric News, not the last three, but over the last
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.61,1:05:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,year in three sections in the neurological studies of intention, attention setting, intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.03,1:05:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's very interesting to see because the whole argument about free will ends up
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.80,1:05:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,as a redundancy and hoisting around in the level of the free 24-20, 4-40 level of the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.55,1:05:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,disease.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.55,1:05:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's like a dissertation, which is very boring because everybody knows all
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.09,1:05:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the arguments for and against free will, you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.50,1:05:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.50,1:05:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And so it has to be transcended.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.50,1:05:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you whether or not it exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.96,1:06:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Free will, as commonly understood, is an existent reality, which is, as I understand it, it's
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.96,1:06:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.96,1:06:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.96,1:06:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to explain it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.40,1:06:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, because psychology would say all decisions are determined.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.40,1:06:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you understand, conditioned and determined and cultural and habitual and neurological
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.76,1:06:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and et cetera, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.32,1:06:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If you operate from the option that you have free will, I think that would serve the highest
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.26,1:06:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic good.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.26,1:06:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That would serve the highest karmic good to operate as though it were a reality to resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.73,1:06:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So I see because that's taking responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.86,1:06:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I see that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.36,1:06:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's because of taking responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.86,1:06:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better to take responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.86,1:06:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.86,1:06:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So you take responsibility and make a mistake than not take responsibility and be correct,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.80,1:06:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in which there may be no karmic merit whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.80,1:06:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes me feel very good.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.17,1:06:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.17,1:06:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.17,1:06:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Suzanne.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.13,1:06:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.13,1:06:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We have only about half an hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.13,1:06:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.13,1:06:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.13,1:07:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.13,1:07:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't that many people left.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.13,1:07:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We're moving along.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.13,1:07:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to get everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.30,1:07:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.30,1:07:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming today.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.71,1:07:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.75,1:07:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,My question has to do with an experience I've had.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.71,1:07:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.71,1:07:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My experience I've had for many years, I can be doing ordinary things during my day.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.90,1:07:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And these words will escape my mouth that I wasn't thinking about at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.30,1:07:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And the words are, I want to go home.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.15,1:07:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go home.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.94,1:07:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And lately, I've just been taking those words as a reminder to come back to context.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.88,1:07:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And come back to the field to remind myself to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.00,1:07:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there something else I should be doing with that?
